quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  36,28,"And We did not send down against his people after him any guest from heaven, nor was it necessary for Us to do so"
  36,29,"It was no more than a single mighty blast, and behold, they were gone"
  36,30,"Unfortunately for these slaves, there does not come a messenger to them that they did not mock"
  36,31,Do they not see how many generations before them We caused to perish? And they will not return to them
  36,32,But each one of them will be brought before Us
  36,33,"A sign for them is the earth that is dead. We give it life, and produce grain from it, of which you eat"
  36,34,"And We produce in it orchards with date palms and vines, and We cause springs to gush forth therein"
  36,35,That they may enjoy the fruits of it. It was not their hands that made this. Will they not then give thanks
  36,36,"Glory be to God, Who created in pairs all things that the earth produces, all of it, and things that they do not know of"
  36,37,"And a sign for them is the night. We withdraw from it the day, and behold, they are plunged into darkness"
  36,38,"And the Sun runs its course for a period determined for it. That is His decree, the Exalted in Might, the All Knowing"
  36,39,"And the Moon, We have ordained for it phases, until it returns like the withered lower part of a date-stalk"
  36,40,"It is not permitted for the Sun to catch the Moon, nor can the night outstrip the day. Each swims along in its own orbit"
  36,41,And a sign for them is that We carried their people through the flood in the loaded Ark
  36,42,And We have created for them similar vessels on which they ride
  36,43,"If it were Our will, We could drown them. Then there would be no helper, nor could they be delivered"
  36,44,"Except by way of mercy from Us, and by way of convenience for a time"
  36,45,"They are told, “Be conscious of that which is before you and that which is after you, in order that you may receive mercy.”"
  36,46,"Not a sign comes to them from among the signs of their Lord, except those from which they turn away"
  36,47,"And when they are told, “Give of that which God has provided you,” the unbelievers say to those who believe, “Shall we feed those whom if God had so willed, He would have fed Himself? You are in nothing but manifest error.”"
  36,48,"Further they say, “When will this promise come to pass, if what you say is true?”"
  36,49,They will not have to wait for anything but a single blast. It will seize them while they are still disputing among themselves
  36,50,"Then no chance will they have with their will to manage their affairs, nor to return to their people"
  36,51,"The trumpet will be sounded, when behold, from their place of rest, people will rush forth to their Lord"
  36,52,"They will say, “Woe to us, who has raised us up from our resting place?” This is what God, the Merciful Benefactor, promised. And true was the word of the messengers.”"
  36,53,"It will be no more than a single blast, and then they will all be brought up before Us"
  36,54,"Then on that day, not a soul will be wronged in the least, and you will be repaid for your past deeds"
  36,55,Indeed on that day the companions of the garden will have joy in all that they do
  36,56,"They and their mates will be in groves of shade, reclining on thrones"
  36,57,"Fruit will be there for them, they will have whatever they call for"
  36,58,"“Peace,” a word from the Lord, Mercifully Redeeming"
  36,59,"“And O you in sin, get away this day"